<h1>With Error Boundary - OnErrorAsync</h1>

<h2>CustomErrorBoundary with OnErrorAsync:</h2>
<CustomErrorBoundary>
    <ChildContent>
        <Divider />
    </ChildContent>
    <ErrorContent Context="ex">
        <div class="error">
            <h3>Custom Error Handler</h3>
            <p><strong>Message:</strong> @ex.Message</p>
            <p><strong>Type:</strong> @ex.GetType().Name</p>
            <p style="color: green;">✓ Error logged to console with timestamp</p>
        </div>
    </ErrorContent>
</CustomErrorBoundary>

<p style="margin-top: 20px; color: gray;">
    The CustomErrorBoundary overrides OnErrorAsync to provide custom error handling logic,
    such as logging errors to a service, sending telemetry, or performing cleanup operations.
</p>
